article.headline: Quinnipiac 64, Fairleigh Dickinson 63
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Adam Gonzalez's free throw with 8.7 seconds left gave Quinnipiac a 64-63 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday night. DeMario Anderson had 17 points, five rebounds, three assists and three steals for Quinnipiac (7-10, 5-3 in Northeast Conference), while Karl Anderson added 15 points and Chris Wehye had 11 points and seven rebounds. Andre Harris finished with 21 points and nine rebounds for the Knights (9-9, 4-3), while Cameron Tyler had 15 points, six rebounds and four assists. The teams traded the lead for most of the game before Tyler's layup tied the score at 63-63 with 38.7 seconds left. Neither team scored again until Gonzalez made one of two free throws attempts to put the Bobcats up for good. FDU then had one last chance as Tyler drove the length of the court, but the Knights could not get a basket before time expired.
